ion is also given to the language-theoretical, grammatical and lexicological spadework that is a necessary prerequisite for any kind of lexicographic practice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 4aDeutsch. 4aLexikographie. 4aWörterbuch. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aBreidt, Elisabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBär, Jochen A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHermanns, Fritz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLemberg, Ingrid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMudersbach, Klaus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPetzold, Sybille, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRipfel, Martha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoe, Ian F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchierholz, Stefan J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSpeer, Heino, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStorrer, Angelika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWiegand, Herbert Ernst, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWiegand, Herbert Ernst, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 1990 - 1999z9783110636895oZDB-23-DLS0 cprintz978348430984540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311091673740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110916737423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110916737/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPD